 "remarks": "Terrific opportunity to own in the desirable Sylvan Knoll Section 2. This two-bedroom townhouse offers a main level with a living room, dining area, and kitchen, ready for your finishing touches. Upstairs are two bedrooms, a full bath with a new bathroom fan, and attic storage for added convenience. The lower level provides flexible space for a family room, office, or recreation area, and the unit is dry, with no basement flooding or water issues. Additional updates include new copper piping for the washer/dryer and a brand-new heating unit. Hardwood floors throughout both levels and central air ensure year-round comfort. Enjoy your own patio, designated parking spots, the ability to garden in front of the unit, and a quiet, tree-lined setting. The HOA fee is $533 and includes taxes, lawn care, snow removal, and maintenance-significantly less than Sylvan Knoll Section 1. Up to two pets are allowed, and the complex is 100% owner-occupied. Ideally located near Cove Island Park and just minutes to downtown Stamford, shopping, and Metro-North.",
